1
00:02:01,450 --> 00:02:06,670
(Pretty Boy)

2
00:02:07,120 --> 00:02:09,600
(Episode 9)

3
00:02:11,270 --> 00:02:12,310
What mourning are you talking about?

4
00:02:13,270 --> 00:02:14,280
Who's mourning?

5
00:02:14,960 --> 00:02:16,230
Aren't you a widow?

6
00:02:16,970 --> 00:02:18,230
Isn't she a widow?

7
00:02:20,280 --> 00:02:23,230
Actually, I am a widow.

8
00:02:23,990 --> 00:02:27,150
My late husband has already passed away.

9
00:02:34,560 --> 00:02:35,710
Yes, right.

10
00:02:42,140 --> 00:02:43,820
I hope you can accept me.

11
00:02:43,840 --> 00:02:45,550
Why are your tactics exactly the same as his?

12
00:02:46,740 --> 00:02:49,270
He already accepted flowers from Young Master Wang last time.

13
00:02:51,329 --> 00:02:52,829
He is a widow.

14
00:02:54,420 --> 00:02:55,750
He can't accept your flowers.

15
00:03:07,230 --> 00:03:07,990
I guess this is it.

16
00:03:09,160 --> 00:03:11,270
We won't be able to go to class today.

17
00:03:12,000 --> 00:03:14,070
So, are we breaking up?

18
00:03:20,079 --> 00:03:21,070
I'll stay a bit longer.

19
00:03:23,220 --> 00:03:24,030
Let's go.

20
00:03:41,740 --> 00:03:43,430
That Hong Hui is really funny.

21
00:03:43,670 --> 00:03:44,670
He actually sent you flowers.

22
00:03:46,210 --> 00:03:48,740
I might have given him some wrong signals.

23
00:03:50,430 --> 00:03:52,030
I've been observing him all day.

24
00:03:52,300 --> 00:03:54,910
You suspect he's the stalker?

25
00:03:55,270 --> 00:03:56,270
He's the most suspicious.

26
00:03:56,710 --> 00:03:59,270
Besides, there are only a few people around Wang Yishao.

27
00:03:59,500 --> 00:04:01,470
So his teaching of the so-called invisibility technique

28
00:04:01,680 --> 00:04:03,630
is actually an intentional cover-up?

29
00:04:04,030 --> 00:04:05,430
Every man has a fool in his sleeve.

30
00:04:05,520 --> 00:04:06,870
This way of covering up

31
00:04:06,980 --> 00:04:08,660
actually exposed his true intentions.

32
00:04:09,210 --> 00:04:11,190
Are there any countermeasures?

33
00:04:13,930 --> 00:04:17,310
How about you use your charms to win him over?

34
00:04:33,280 --> 00:04:35,909
Wang Yishao seems to like Gan Pu a lot.

35
00:04:37,900 --> 00:04:39,590
Looks like you've known for a while.

36
00:04:40,420 --> 00:04:42,510
This was my first time having deep interaction with you all.

37
00:04:42,610 --> 00:04:45,390
You seem a bit... Jealous?

38
00:04:47,140 --> 00:04:49,030
I feel that between her and me,

39
00:04:49,920 --> 00:04:50,950
it's probably impossible.

40
00:04:51,560 --> 00:04:53,710
You haven't actually fallen for Gan Pu, have you?

41
00:04:59,540 --> 00:05:01,750
We have so many important things to do.

42
00:05:02,680 --> 00:05:03,670
I've got no time

43
00:05:03,950 --> 00:05:06,350
to be caught up in such romantic entanglements.

44
00:05:11,820 --> 00:05:13,510
So what should we do now?

45
00:05:18,100 --> 00:05:19,190
Let's analyze the situation.

46
00:05:19,610 --> 00:05:21,230
Go collect a few props for me.

47
00:05:21,620 --> 00:05:22,430
Okay.

48
00:05:35,060 --> 00:05:36,670
This is the Mo Clan.

49
00:05:37,230 --> 00:05:38,310
The one specialized in slingshots.

50
00:05:41,650 --> 00:05:42,990
This is Mingyi Manor.

51
00:05:43,940 --> 00:05:44,800
Kill.

52
00:05:45,770 --> 00:05:46,790
This is the General.

53
00:05:46,930 --> 00:05:48,030
That's us.

54
00:05:48,260 --> 00:05:49,430
We have armor.

55
00:05:51,100 --> 00:05:52,390
This is Wang Quan.

56
00:05:53,580 --> 00:05:54,470
It's the only one left.

57
00:05:55,040 --> 00:05:58,030
The Mo Clan and Mingyi Manor are enemies.

58
00:05:59,010 --> 00:06:01,990
The Mo Clan and the General are also adversaries.

59
00:06:02,180 --> 00:06:04,810
The General and Mingyi Manor are enemies.

60
00:06:04,910 --> 00:06:06,030
But Mingyi Manor

61
00:06:06,030 --> 00:06:08,740
is actually in a cooperative relationship with Wang Quan.

62
00:06:08,990 --> 00:06:11,550
The enemy of my enemy is my friend.

63
00:06:12,150 --> 00:06:15,040
So we should be allies with the Mo Clan, right?

64
00:06:15,140 --> 00:06:17,280
But for some reason, Wang Yishao thinks

65
00:06:17,360 --> 00:06:20,430
that we and the Mo Clan are enemies.

66
00:06:21,000 --> 00:06:22,670
We and the Mo Clan...

67
00:06:23,320 --> 00:06:26,150
We and the Mo Clan are enemies?

68
00:06:27,480 --> 00:06:28,790
Judging from Mingyi Manor's

69
00:06:28,790 --> 00:06:30,510
previous attitude towards my father,

70
00:06:30,900 --> 00:06:33,830
Mingyi Manor must be our enemy.

71
00:06:34,250 --> 00:06:35,270
Not just enemies,

72
00:06:35,450 --> 00:06:36,680
but mortal enemies.

73
00:06:38,520 --> 00:06:41,310
But after learning about your identity as the former Emperor's son,

74
00:06:41,520 --> 00:06:44,060
Mingyi Manor's attitude towards my father has changed.

75
00:06:44,680 --> 00:06:47,670
Could it be that you're not on our side either?

76
00:06:49,280 --> 00:06:50,670
Many alliances would

77
00:06:50,720 --> 00:06:52,430
change due to interests.

78
00:06:53,190 --> 00:06:54,460
There are no eternal enemies,

79
00:06:54,740 --> 00:06:56,230
nor eternal friends.

80
00:06:59,600 --> 00:07:01,550
All the information we've received

81
00:07:01,860 --> 00:07:03,230
might be inaccurate.

82
00:07:13,700 --> 00:07:15,270
Gao Yin works for Wang,

83
00:07:15,510 --> 00:07:17,750
but she hasn't made a move against us yet.

84
00:07:18,140 --> 00:07:19,670
That's really strange.

85
00:07:20,820 --> 00:07:23,140
Should we continue to test Mingyi Manor?

86
00:07:23,160 --> 00:07:24,030
It's necessary.

87
00:07:24,480 --> 00:07:27,280
Father revealed the information that I'm the former Emperor's son.

88
00:07:27,630 --> 00:07:29,000
It's obvious that the information he knows

89
00:07:29,000 --> 00:07:30,390
is much more than what we know.

90
00:07:30,580 --> 00:07:32,360
But since we don't have this information,

91
00:07:32,360 --> 00:07:33,950
we can't immediately know

92
00:07:33,950 --> 00:07:35,190
what to do next.

93
00:07:35,450 --> 00:07:36,710
What we can do now

94
00:07:36,710 --> 00:07:38,150
is to get closer to Mingyi Manor.

95
00:07:38,680 --> 00:07:41,020
If we could find Father, that would be best.

96
00:07:41,050 --> 00:07:42,830
This way, we can learn more information.

97
00:07:43,240 --> 00:07:44,510
Let's go find Yinniang.

98
00:07:44,890 --> 00:07:46,390
But Yinniang is no ordinary person.

99
00:07:46,540 --> 00:07:47,870
Completely false information...

100
00:07:48,730 --> 00:07:50,000
She probably won't fall for it.

101
00:07:50,190 --> 00:07:51,310
Then what should we do?

102
00:07:51,810 --> 00:07:54,100
We can't just tell her I'm with the General.

103
00:07:54,180 --> 00:07:55,790
Wouldn't that be walking right into the trap?

104
00:07:58,100 --> 00:08:00,530
Do you remember how we

105
00:08:00,550 --> 00:08:01,870
tricked you before?

106
00:08:03,090 --> 00:08:04,790
A friend of the former Emperor's son.

107
00:08:05,160 --> 00:08:06,870
Judging from our previous actions,

108
00:08:06,910 --> 00:08:07,970
it doesn't seem like the General

109
00:08:08,000 --> 00:08:09,740
or any other faction is behind it.

110
00:08:10,010 --> 00:08:12,070
Using this identity would indeed be safer for you.

111
00:08:12,130 --> 00:08:13,630
And we're telling the truth.

112
00:08:15,050 --> 00:08:18,390
What if they capture me

113
00:08:18,420 --> 00:08:19,550
and interrogate me through torture?

114
00:08:19,630 --> 00:08:20,820
What should I do then?

115
00:08:20,960 --> 00:08:22,990
Treating Father well isn't a trap, is it?

116
00:08:23,110 --> 00:08:25,510
They're not even torturing Father anymore. Why would they torture you?

117
00:08:25,920 --> 00:08:26,630
That's right.

118
00:08:27,310 --> 00:08:28,310
I'll go right away.

119
00:08:28,590 --> 00:08:29,230
Wait.

120
00:08:29,250 --> 00:08:30,240
Don't be hasty.

121
00:08:30,270 --> 00:08:31,210
Let me tell you about

122
00:08:31,230 --> 00:08:33,230
what kind of person Mr. Shang Shan is.

123
00:08:47,570 --> 00:08:48,350
Teacher.

124
00:08:48,380 --> 00:08:50,470
Why are you always doing such weird things?

125
00:08:50,730 --> 00:08:52,710
How dirty the dew water is.

126
00:08:52,970 --> 00:08:54,670
Not to mention it's covered in dust,

127
00:08:54,730 --> 00:08:57,230
before you take a sip of it,

128
00:08:57,340 --> 00:08:58,740
the insects, spiders,

129
00:08:58,960 --> 00:09:00,710
flies, and mosquitoes have all taken a sip of it.

130
00:09:01,850 --> 00:09:03,590
Why is your mouth so foul?

131
00:09:04,010 --> 00:09:05,180
Every word you say stinks.

132
00:09:05,210 --> 00:09:06,070
Who taught you that?

133
00:09:06,860 --> 00:09:08,510
Well, you are my teacher.

134
00:09:10,360 --> 00:09:11,670
Fine, I won't sip it anymore.

135
00:09:13,500 --> 00:09:14,800
Keep it. Hey.

136
00:09:14,830 --> 00:09:16,440
Keep it to collect the dew tomorrow.

137
00:09:16,460 --> 00:09:18,840
I've thrown it away 5,874 times.

138
00:09:20,450 --> 00:09:21,830
As expected of my master.

139
00:09:22,240 --> 00:09:23,480
Your persistent pursuit

140
00:09:23,480 --> 00:09:25,190
is truly awe-inspiring.

141
00:09:25,590 --> 00:09:27,190
Today is the last time.

142
00:09:27,490 --> 00:09:29,360
You're finally kicking me out?

143
00:09:30,430 --> 00:09:32,430
It's not that I'm kicking you out,

144
00:09:32,500 --> 00:09:34,870
but I'm kicking myself out.

145
00:09:36,300 --> 00:09:37,900
You've finally had enough of me.

146
00:09:38,590 --> 00:09:40,150
I've taught you for 15 years,

147
00:09:40,390 --> 00:09:42,110
and played the fool for 15 years.

148
00:09:42,260 --> 00:09:43,630
It's time to set you free.

149
00:09:44,020 --> 00:09:45,230
You've already said this

150
00:09:45,230 --> 00:09:47,110
3,285 times.

151
00:09:48,010 --> 00:09:49,790
That wasn't the number yesterday.

152
00:09:49,970 --> 00:09:51,750
Anyone can make up numbers on the spot.

153
00:09:54,930 --> 00:09:55,840
People

154
00:09:56,560 --> 00:09:58,110
always need to grow.

155
00:09:58,130 --> 00:10:00,630
This time, you'll have to face it alone.

156
00:10:10,360 --> 00:10:11,670
You're serious this time.

157
00:10:42,370 --> 00:10:43,790
In that sense,

158
00:10:44,160 --> 00:10:46,550
your master doesn't really seem like a transcendent being.

159
00:10:46,950 --> 00:10:48,310
He even ghosted you.

160
00:10:48,460 --> 00:10:48,870
To be precise,

161
00:10:49,050 --> 00:10:50,490
he was never like a transcendent being to begin with.

162
00:10:50,510 --> 00:10:51,990
The main goal is to make Yinniang believe you.

163
00:11:05,680 --> 00:11:07,790
I heard you brought us some important news.

164
00:11:08,680 --> 00:11:09,470
Yes.

165
00:11:10,080 --> 00:11:12,110
I've found out the identities of those rescuers from yesterday.

166
00:11:12,380 --> 00:11:13,710
I specially came here to inform you.

167
00:11:14,240 --> 00:11:15,390
Who are they?

168
00:11:16,480 --> 00:11:18,950
The person you captured has an adopted son.

169
00:11:19,370 --> 00:11:20,990
They are friends of that adopted son.

170
00:11:21,220 --> 00:11:22,310
How do you know this?

171
00:11:22,420 --> 00:11:23,590
I'm also his friend.

172
00:11:23,680 --> 00:11:25,520
So you knew about the operation in advance?

173
00:11:26,510 --> 00:11:28,270
I... Didn't know.

174
00:11:30,160 --> 00:11:32,900
I came in here to get information.

175
00:11:32,980 --> 00:11:35,120
My mission was to find the location and tell them.

176
00:11:35,170 --> 00:11:36,430
To avoid exposure,

177
00:11:36,600 --> 00:11:38,110
I didn't participate in the operation.

178
00:11:39,560 --> 00:11:40,710
That's contradictory.

179
00:11:41,270 --> 00:11:43,270
Then why are you exposing yourself now?

180
00:11:44,340 --> 00:11:46,910
I've just come to a realization.

181
00:11:47,290 --> 00:11:50,190
I think we might not be enemies.

182
00:11:51,620 --> 00:11:52,790
Why would you think that?

183
00:11:52,900 --> 00:11:53,790
Intuition.

184
00:11:55,050 --> 00:11:56,910
What's the name of that adopted son?

185
00:11:58,790 --> 00:12:00,970
I can't tell you his name.

186
00:12:01,190 --> 00:12:03,420
I came here on my own initiative this time,

187
00:12:03,860 --> 00:12:05,350
without obtaining his consent.

188
00:12:05,980 --> 00:12:07,990
What's his identity?

189
00:12:15,520 --> 00:12:16,990
The son of the former Emperor.

190
00:12:18,370 --> 00:12:19,510
How do you know that?

191
00:12:23,030 --> 00:12:24,550
From Mr. Shang Shan.

192
00:12:25,030 --> 00:12:26,320
Mr. Shang Shan?

193
00:12:26,550 --> 00:12:28,310
That's not someone you could casually meet.

194
00:12:29,060 --> 00:12:30,670
The son of the former Emperor took me there.

195
00:12:30,750 --> 00:12:31,910
Of course he would meet me.

196
00:12:33,030 --> 00:12:35,550
So what does Mr. Shang Shan look like?

197
00:12:38,390 --> 00:12:39,830
He's an old peasant.

198
00:12:40,270 --> 00:12:41,950
He doesn't have any mystical aura around him.

199
00:12:42,470 --> 00:12:44,630
He doesn't look like a famous person at all.

200
00:12:45,110 --> 00:12:46,110
You're just making this up.

201
00:12:46,320 --> 00:12:47,110
It's true.

202
00:12:50,010 --> 00:12:51,510
What do you want?

203
00:12:54,550 --> 00:12:56,270
I want to see the person you've captured.

204
00:12:57,360 --> 00:12:58,510
To ensure he's unharmed.

205
00:13:01,450 --> 00:13:02,390
Not now.

206
00:13:02,580 --> 00:13:04,390
There's no trust between us yet.

207
00:13:04,920 --> 00:13:07,670
Bring that son of the former Emperor here first.

208
00:13:09,250 --> 00:13:10,230
As you said,

209
00:13:10,420 --> 00:13:11,870
we don't trust each other.

210
00:13:12,310 --> 00:13:14,670
The son of the former Emperor is my last card.

211
00:13:15,550 --> 00:13:16,870
I can't tell you now.

212
00:13:23,250 --> 00:13:24,150
Alright then.

213
00:13:24,630 --> 00:13:25,750
We can wait.

214
00:13:30,270 --> 00:13:31,600
Then wait.

215
00:13:32,110 --> 00:13:34,150
I hope you can trust me soon.

216
00:13:34,410 --> 00:13:35,390
I'll take my leave now.

217
00:13:41,130 --> 00:13:44,230
Are they in cahoots with that captive?

218
00:13:44,450 --> 00:13:45,860
They were there to rescue him.

219
00:13:46,070 --> 00:13:47,930
Otherwise, they couldn't have triggered the mechanism.

220
00:13:48,480 --> 00:13:51,060
So it's impossible they conspired in the cell.

221
00:13:51,230 --> 00:13:52,230
Let's wait.

222
00:13:52,300 --> 00:13:54,030
See who loses patience first.

223
00:13:55,770 --> 00:13:56,550
By the way,

224
00:13:56,700 --> 00:13:58,030
should we arrange for someone

225
00:13:58,080 --> 00:13:59,550
to renovate their living quarters?

226
00:13:59,710 --> 00:14:01,470
So they don't have to be cramped together.

227
00:14:01,790 --> 00:14:04,150
We're short-handed. Everyone's out searching.

228
00:14:05,890 --> 00:14:06,950
Try to renovate as much as possible.

229
00:14:07,050 --> 00:14:08,510
Letting them live together

230
00:14:08,510 --> 00:14:10,150
was meant to keep them in check, wasn't it?

231
00:14:10,320 --> 00:14:12,430
It seems that's not working at all now.

232
00:14:12,510 --> 00:14:13,950
Gao Yin does whatever she wants.

233
00:14:14,130 --> 00:14:15,750
Hu Jiao is just a fool.

234
00:14:16,800 --> 00:14:18,490
Since that son of the former Emperor

235
00:14:18,520 --> 00:14:20,230
wants them to have better living conditions,

236
00:14:20,920 --> 00:14:22,590
let's grant his wish.

237
00:14:22,940 --> 00:14:23,630
Yes.

238
00:14:23,940 --> 00:14:26,070
When you have time, go to the town more often.

239
00:14:27,110 --> 00:14:28,910
Take Han Aizhen with you.

240
00:14:29,150 --> 00:14:29,910
Yes.

241
00:14:34,300 --> 00:14:35,470
It rains a lot in the mountains.

242
00:14:35,770 --> 00:14:37,190
You should be more careful about safety in the future.

243
00:14:43,570 --> 00:14:44,770
Are you from the Mo Clan?

244
00:14:52,760 --> 00:14:54,360
I want to ask you a sensitive question.

245
00:14:54,780 --> 00:14:55,910
You don't have to answer.

246
00:14:56,860 --> 00:14:57,900
Over these years,

247
00:14:58,280 --> 00:15:00,190
have you joined any organizations?

248
00:15:00,670 --> 00:15:02,110
Since you've asked,

249
00:15:02,900 --> 00:15:04,630
I'll also ask you a sensitive question.

250
00:15:05,110 --> 00:15:06,240
You don't have to answer either.

251
00:15:07,180 --> 00:15:09,520
You want to be an extraordinary person so much,

252
00:15:09,550 --> 00:15:11,310
so why did you come to Mingyi Manor

253
00:15:11,710 --> 00:15:14,710
and join this whirlpool of right and wrong?

254
00:15:20,520 --> 00:15:22,950
For the little bit of family affection that remains, I suppose.

255
00:15:24,590 --> 00:15:25,430
Be careful.

256
00:15:27,670 --> 00:15:28,510
Did you get it?

257
00:15:29,730 --> 00:15:31,310
I got it! I got it!

258
00:15:31,900 --> 00:15:32,600
Awesome!

259
00:15:32,950 --> 00:15:34,030
Come on, get down.

260
00:15:52,900 --> 00:15:55,100
Green plain, red bridge, same as the good old days,

261
00:15:56,890 --> 00:15:57,830
yet the person is not seen,

262
00:15:59,200 --> 00:16:02,270
and water flows in vain.

263
00:16:03,080 --> 00:16:04,630
The imperial family is the most heartless of all.

264
00:16:05,290 --> 00:16:06,310
When you grow up,

265
00:16:07,600 --> 00:16:10,710
you have no choice but to let a part of yourself die.

266
00:16:12,230 --> 00:16:14,390
For that bit of obsession you can't let go,

267
00:16:15,060 --> 00:16:17,540
like clinging to the most beautiful things in the mortal world.

268
00:16:19,950 --> 00:16:21,350
I can understand you a little now.

269
00:16:24,260 --> 00:16:25,070
Tell us,

270
00:16:25,570 --> 00:16:26,750
why did you come here?

271
00:16:27,470 --> 00:16:28,110
Of course,

272
00:16:28,560 --> 00:16:29,790
you still don't have to answer.

273
00:16:32,440 --> 00:16:33,320
Me?

274
00:16:34,890 --> 00:16:36,510
I'm here because of someone else's obsession.

275
00:16:37,350 --> 00:16:38,790
It's a long story, anyway.

276
00:16:39,100 --> 00:16:41,550
I'll tell you more if there's a chance in the future.

277
00:16:42,960 --> 00:16:44,110
As long as there is a future.

278
00:16:45,500 --> 00:16:46,710
What I mean is,

279
00:16:47,630 --> 00:16:49,190
